---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Outreach" description="Public engagement: the Hannah Arendt Institute, public lectures, the PACT School Tour, and media appearances.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Outreach</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        As a publicly funded researcher, I believe research should serve the broader society. Through public lectures, school visits, media engagement, 
        and my work with the Hannah Arendt Institute, I try to make academic knowledge about polarisation and democracy accessible and actionable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HAI -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <img src="/images/hai-logo.svg" alt="Hannah Arendt Instituut logo" style="height: 48px; width: auto;" />
        <span style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-faint); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase;">Hannah Arendt Instituut</span>
      </div>
      <h2>Senior academic fellow</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannah Arendt Institute</a> for diversity, urbanity, and citizenship started as a collaboration between VUB and UAntwerpen, but currently involves all Flemish universities as a bridging organisation between civil society, political practice and academia. It combines scientific knowledge about citizenship, urban life, and diversity with the practices and insights of policymakers, organisations, and citizens.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a member of the <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/samenwerken/onderzoeker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">academic team</a>, I help organise academic and public events, bring expertise on polarisation and democratic resilience to the Institute. As the Institute connects civil society actors, it creates valuable opportunities to present my research to broader audiences through public events. It is also a place where I learn to translate academic work into accessible language — giving research meaning beyond the academy. <a href="mailto:kamil.bernaerts@hannah-arendt.institute">Contact me</a>.
      </p>
      <p><a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/project/democratie-en-polarisatie/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View my HAI profile →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INVITE ME — expanded speaking section -->
  <section class="section" id="invite">
    <div class="container">
      <span style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-faint); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase;">Public engagement</span>
      <h2>Lectures &amp; workshops</h2>
      <p>
        I give lectures, workshops, and panel contributions on polarisation, democracy, and critical thinking for a wide range of audiences: 
        trade unions, local governments, civil society organisations, schools, media professionals, corporate teams, and the general public. 
        Every talk is tailored to the audience and grounded in the latest political science research.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Topics I speak on</h3>
      <div class="pub-list">
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div>
            <p class="pub-title">Polarisation &amp; democracy</p>
            <p class="pub-authors">Does polarisation really undermine democracy? What does the research say, and what can we do about it?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div>
            <p class="pub-title">Affective polarisation</p>
            <p class="pub-authors">Why do we dislike people who vote differently? The psychology and politics of us-versus-them thinking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div>
            <p class="pub-title">Institutional design &amp; conflict</p>
            <p class="pub-authors">How do political institutions shape the way societies deal with deep disagreement? Lessons from Belgium and beyond.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Formats</h3>
      <p>
        Keynote lecture (45–60 min) · Interactive workshop (half day) · Panel discussion or debate · Q&amp;A session following a lecture · 
        School guest lecture (adapted for secondary education) · Custom format on request.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Selected appearances</h3>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.vub.be/nl/nieuws/vub-pact-school-tour-caroline-pauwels-atheneum-polarisatie" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VUB PACT School Tour</a> (Caroline Pauwels Academy of Critical Thinking) · 
        <a href="https://checkfirst.network/event/lunch-lecture-with-kamil-bernaerts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EDMO BELUX Lunch Lecture</a> · 
        <a href="https://puc.kuleuven.be/nl/opleiding/polarisatie-8adjxg90jwgep574/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KU Leuven Metaforum</a> on polarisation · 
        Public events via the Hannah Arendt Institute.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px; background: var(--color-bg-soft, #fafafa);">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.05rem;">
          <strong>Interested in inviting me?</strong> I am available for lectures, workshops, and panel contributions in Dutch and English. 
          <a href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PUBLIC WRITING -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-faint); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase;">Public writing</span>
      <h2>Essays &amp; public writing</h2>
      <p>
        Alongside academic publications, I write accessible essays and commentaries on polarisation, democracy, and current affairs. 
        These pieces appear on my <a href="/writing/">writing page</a> and are occasionally republished.
      </p>
      <div class="pub-list">
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div>
            <p class="pub-title"><a href="/writing/vdem-2025-nl/">De autocratiserende tsunami is aan land gekomen in het Westen</a></p>
            <p class="pub-authors">kamilbernaerts.com · republished by <a href="https://hannah-arendt.institute/nieuws/autocratisering-westen-democratie-wereldwijd-onder-druk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannah Arendt Instituut</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="pub-meta"><p class="pub-year">2026</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p><a href="/writing/">All writing →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IN THE MEDIA -->
